20a%20full%20ride%20to%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%20in%20Urbana-Champaign%20to%20pursue%20a%20masters%20in%20aerospace%20engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20challenge%20before%20Akshata%20presented%20itself%20in%20the%20form%20of%20getting%20an%20aerospace%20job%20in%20the%20US%20without%20a%20citizenship%20or%20a%20green%20card.%20To%20be%20accepted%20as%20a%20doctoral%20candidate%20at%20MIT%2C%20she%20would%20need%20some%20work%20experience%2C%20she%20learned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20came%20here%20alone%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20support.%20I%20kept%20doing%20research%20projects%20and%20publishing%20papers%20to%20add%20to%20my%20credentials%20to%20show%20that%20I%20can%20create%20an%20impact.%20Every%20opportunity%20I%20got%20was%20never%20luck%20or%20coincidence%2C%20it%20was%20through%20hard%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20engineer%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20pursuing%20her%20masters%2C%20she%20started%20writing%20to%20professors%20at%20MIT%20that%20she%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20them%20for%20her%20PhD.%20It%20was%20only%20on%20her%20third%20attempt%20that%20she%20was%20selected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20honed%20my%20skills%20and%20worked%20outside%20my%20curriculum%20but%20was%20still%20waitlisted%20as%20not%20all%20space%20projects%20can%20take%20foreign%20nationals%20since%20they%20are%20funded%20by%20the%20US%20government%20and%20have%20restrictions.%20But%20when%20I%20was%20waitlisted%20the%20second%20time%2C%20I%20wrote%20to%20all%20the%20professors%20at%20MIT%20asking%20for%20a%20chance%20to%20work%20with%20them%20for%20a%20year.%20Finally%2C%20I%20heard%20back%20from%20professor%20Sara%20Seager%20that%20there%20was%20a%20project%20I%20could%20work%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Seager%20is%20an%20astrophysicist%20and%20planetary%20scientist%20at%20MIT%20who%20focuses%20on%20exoplanet%20research%2C%20which%20is%20the%20discovery%20of%20new%20planets.%20She%20offered%20her%20a%20temporary%20research%20associate%20position%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20Akshata%20had%20two%20options%20%E2%80%94%20take%20a%20well-paying%20job%20at%20the%20likes%20of%20Google%20or%20Amazon%20without%20worrying%20about%20her%20visa%20or%20career%2C%20or%20take%20a%20risk%20and%20work%20on%20a%20new%20research%20project%20which%20was%20incredibly%20exciting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20no-brainer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC6Y47dFR7g5%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC6Y47dFR7g5%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC6Y47dFR7g5%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Dr.%20Akshata%20Krishnamurthy%20%7C%20NASA%20Rocket%20Scientist%20(%40astro.akshata)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20for%20a%20year%20on%20exoplanet%20research%2C%20she%20applied%20to%20the%20MIT%20PhD%20programme%20again%2C%20and%20as%20they%20say%2C%20third%20time%E2%80%99s%20the%20charm.%20Under%20Professor%20Seager%2C%20and%20in%20a%20fully-funded%20programme%2C%20she%20finally%20got%20her%20PhD%20in%202020.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20doctorate%20is%20in%20aeronautics%20and%20astronautics%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20I%20worked%20on%20the%20boundary%20of%20science%20and%20engineering%2C%20focusing%20on%20developing%20space%20telescopes%20and%20technologies%20to%20discover%20new%20planets%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20went%20on%20to%20work%20full-time%20at%20the%20NASA%20JPL%2C%20which%2C%20she%20shares%2C%20was%20also%20a%20serendipitous%20occurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20worked%20there%20for%20three%20months%20as%20an%20intern%20and%20would%20meet%20with%20managers%20everyday%20asking%20for%20a%20job.%20But%20nobody%20could%20commit%20anything%20to%20me%20without%20a%20green%20card%20as%20it%20involves%20a%20lot%20of%20paperwork%20and%20complexity%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20day%20of%20her%20internship%20arrived%20but%20she%20still%20had%20no%20job%20offers%20or%20interviews.%20Luckily%2C%20she%20had%20a%20presentation%20to%20give%20that%20day.%20A%20hiring%20manager%20in%20the%20audience%20was%20impressed%20with%20Akshata%E2%80%99s%20presentation%20and%20decided%20to%20give%20her%20a%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20then%2C%20till%20the%20paperwork%20came%20through%2C%20the%20scientist%20recalls%20that%20she%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20breathe%20easy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20entered%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F323066%2Fchandrayaan-3-the-history-of-how-india-began-one-of-its-most-significant-space-journeys%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%20JPL%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20employee%20in%20February%202020%2C%20that%20was%20one%20of%20the%20happiest%20days%20of%20her%20life.%C2%A0%